<paragraph blockId="4.[227,1437,441,584]" box="[227,345,441,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,345,441,467]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,345,441,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[227,1437,441,584]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[371,498,488,513]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Ballomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erasmus">
<emphasis box="[371,498,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">B. erasmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. et sp. nov. is easily recognized by the field of spines in front of the epigastric fold and the RTA with three short elements. The female is characterized by the S-shaped ducts in the anterior half of the epigyne.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
