<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1436,351,447]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
MEASUREMENTS. Total length 4.97; carapace 2.63 long, 0.99 high, 1.85 wide, narrowed to 
<quantity box="[1302,1386,386,413]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.159" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="in" value="0.85">0.85 in</quantity>
eye region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1436,487,654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
COLOURATION. Carapace (
<figureCitation box="[524,591,487,513]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="4.[227,270,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Ballomma erasmus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. Prosoma, ventral view. D. Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3471684" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3471684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[592,618,487,513]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A</collectionCode>
) medium brown without silvery setae; chelicerae medium brown in basal half, pale brown in distal half, sternum brownish orange (
<figureCitation box="[963,1028,522,548]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="4.[227,270,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Ballomma erasmus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. Prosoma, ventral view. D. Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3471684" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3471684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[1028,1049,522,548]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[1068,1090,522,548]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C</collectionCode>
); legs uniform pale yellowish brown, femora with greenish tinge; abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[768,832,557,584]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="4.[227,270,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Ballomma erasmus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. Prosoma, ventral view. D. Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3471684" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3471684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[832,856,558,584]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[874,894,558,584]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[906,931,558,584]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">D</collectionCode>
): dorsum and sides pale with complex dark pattern; venter pale, yellowish sclerotized areas in front of spinnerets and in front of epigastric fold; spinnerets pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1437,693,790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
CARAPACE (
<figureCitation box="[359,434,693,719]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="4.[227,270,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[227,1437,801,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Ballomma erasmus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. Prosoma, ventral view. D. Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3471684" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3471684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[434,455,693,719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A</collectionCode>
, 2 
<collectionCode box="[486,507,694,720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">D</collectionCode>
). Smooth, strongly narrowed in front; flat, fovea long, in shallow depression. Chilum double, each sclerite 0.05 high, 0.13 wide; no setae. Sternum shield-shaped, 1.07 long, 0.85 wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1437,829,891]" box="[227,1437,829,856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading allCaps="true" box="[227,1437,829,856]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="5">
EYES. 
<collectionCode box="[297,367,829,855]" collectionName="USA, Florida, Gainesville, University of Florida, Florida Museum of Natural History, Allyn Museum" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">AME</collectionCode>
: 0.08; ALE: 0.11; ALE–ALE: 0.00; 
<collectionCode box="[793,860,829,855]" collectionName="USA, Florida, Gainesville, University of Florida, Florida Museum of Natural History, Allyn Museum" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">AME</collectionCode>
–ALE: 0.05; PME: 0.10; PLE: 0.12; PME–PME:
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1437,829,891]" box="[227,1211,864,891]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">0.03; PME–PLE: 0.13. Clypeus 0.21 or 2.6 times width of ALE, strongly retreating.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1206,930,956]" box="[227,1206,930,956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">LEGS. Anterior tarsi shorter than metatarsi and fusiform; hinged hairs on TI and TII.</paragraph>
